SP  - 545
EP  - 557
VL  - 41
IS  - 3
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1986.tb04514.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT This paper derives a framework for arbitrage models in markets with frictions. It generalizes the existence of a valuation operator to such markets. As in perfect markets, the valuation operator is a linear operator and its existence is implied by the no-arbitrage condition. In imperfect markets the valuation operator is individual-specific and depends on the agent's position in the market. The methodology employed in the paper is duality in convex programming.
ER  - 

